        tool_input:
            description: Explore chat message UI code
            prompt: |-
                Explore the Swift chat message display code in the Orchestra macOS app. I need to understand:

                1. **ChatMessage model** — the message struct, roles (user/assistant), content field, any streaming-related fields. Search in apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Plugins/ChatPlugin/

                2. **ChatSession model** — session struct, bridgeSessionId, metadata. Same directory.

                3. **ChatView / ChatMessageView / ChatBubbleView** — how messages are displayed, any existing bubble styling, markdown rendering. Search in apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Plugins/ChatPlugin/ and apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Components/

                4. **MarkdownContentView** — how markdown/text is rendered in chat responses. File: apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Components/MarkdownContentView.swift

                5. **Any existing status bar, metadata display, or token count UI** in the chat area.

