        tool_response:
            agentId: abb8e37a0a3c74568
            content:
                - text: "Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive summary of the chat message display code in the Orchestra Swift app.\n\n## Swift Chat Message Display Code Exploration — Complete Analysis\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the Orchestra macOS app's chat implementation, here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **ChatMessage Model** (`OrchestraKit/Models/Models.swift`, lines 222-267)\n\n```swift\npublic struct ChatMessage: Identifiable, Codable, Hashable, Sendable {\n    public var id: UUID\n    public var sessionId: UUID\n    public var role: MessageRole        // .user, .assistant, .system\n    public var content: String          // Message text (markdown for assistant)\n    public var toolCalls: [ToolCall]    // Tool invocations (parsed from content)\n    public var pendingQuestion: UserQuestion?  // Interactive question (requires answer)\n    public var createdAt: Date\n}\n```\n\n**Key fields:**\n- `role`: enum `.user | .assistant | .system`\n- `content`: Raw text/markdown (metadata like \"Model:\", \"Tokens:\", etc. is extracted before storing)\n- `toolCalls`: Array of executed tools with status (completed/error/running)\n- `pendingQuestion`: Optional interactive question card that the user must answer\n- No streaming fields (streaming is handled in bridge session, not in message model)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **ChatSession Model** (`OrchestraKit/Models/Models.swift`, lines 269-378)\n\n```swift\npublic struct ChatSession: Identifiable, Codable, Hashable, Sendable {\n    public var id: UUID\n    public var title: String\n    public var provider: String         // \"claude\" (provider name)\n    public var isPinned: Bool\n    public var colorName: String        // Named color token: \"red\", \"blue\", etc.\n    public var iconName: String         // SF Symbol override\n    public var createdAt: Date\n    public var messages: [ChatMessage]\n    public var bridgeSessionId: String? // \"s-XXXXXX\" (nil until first message)\n    public var model: String            // \"claude-sonnet-4-6\", \"claude-opus-4-6\", etc.\n    public var mode: String             // \"auto\", \"plan\", \"manual\" (permission mode)\n    public var thinkingEnabled: Bool    // Extended thinking flag\n}\n```\n\n**Key features:**\n- Bridge session ID is lazy-created on first message send\n- Model and mode are configurable per-session\n- Thinking (extended thinking) can be toggled per-session\n- Pinning keeps sessions at top of list (sorted by pinned status, then date)\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Message Display Views**\n\n#### **A. ChatBubble** (`ChatPlugin.swift`, lines 1845-1927)\nMain bubble rendering for individual messages:\n\n```swift\nstruct ChatBubble: View {\n    let message: ChatMessage\n    var onQuestionAnswer: ((UUID, String) -> Void)? = nil\n    // - User messages: light-on-blue background, text only\n    // - Assistant messages: dark background with:\n    //   ├─ Tool call cards (above markdown)\n    //   ├─ MarkdownContentView (main content)\n    //   ├─ UserQuestionCardView (interactive Q&A)\n    //   └─ TTS speaker button (macOS only)\n}\n```\n\n**Layout:**\n- **User**: Right-aligned, blue accent background, rounded 16pt\n- **Assistant**: Left-aligned, gray background, rounded 16pt\n  - Tool calls rendered as collapsible cards above content\n  - Markdown content with full rendering\n  - Interactive question card if present\n  - TTS button in bottom-right (macOS)\n\n---\n\n#### **B. MarkdownContentView** (`Components/MarkdownContentView.swift`)\n\nPure SwiftUI markdown parser with NO WKWebView or network calls:\n\n```swift\nstruct MarkdownContentView: View {\n    let markdown: String\n    var compact: Bool = false\n    // Renders block types: paragraph, heading, codeBlock, blockquote, list, horizontalRule\n}\n```\n\n**Features:**\n- **Headings** (# to ######): Sized by level (20pt H1 → 14pt H6), semibold\n- **Bold/italic/strikethrough**: Via `AttributedString(markdown:options:)` \n- **Inline code**: Rendered inline\n- **Links**: Clickable via attributed string\n- **Fenced code blocks**: Dark background (0.35 opacity black), language label, **Copy button**\n  - Code uses monospaced font, 12pt size\n  - Horizontal scroll for long lines\n- **Blockquotes**: Left border (3pt, 0.4 opacity secondary), indented\n- **Lists** (unordered/ordered): Proper bullet/number formatting, 3pt spacing\n- **Horizontal rules**: Divider with 4pt padding\n\n**No regex**, pure character-by-character parsing.\n\n---\n\n#### **C. MessageList** (`ChatPlugin.swift`, lines 1329-1366)\nScrollable chat history with auto-scroll:\n\n```swift\nstruct MessageList: View {\n    let session: ChatSession\n    var isSending: Bool\n    var loadingWord: String\n    \n    // ScrollViewReader auto-scrolls to last message\n    // onChange: [session.messages.count] → scrollTo(last.id)\n    // onChange: [isSending] → scrollTo(\"typing-indicator\")\n}\n```\n\n**Animation:**\n- Smooth scroll-to-bottom on new messages\n- `.easeOut(duration: 0.2)` animation\n- Shows `TypingIndicator` while sending\n\n---\n\n#### **D. TypingIndicator** (`ChatPlugin.swift`, lines 1370-1405)\n\n```swift\nprivate struct TypingIndicator: View {\n    var loadingWord: String = \"Thinking\"\n    // Shows: \"Thinking.\", \"Thinking..\", \"Thinking...\"\n    // Cycles every 0.5s (3 states = 1.5s per cycle)\n    // Uses cyan→purple gradient with pulse animation\n}\n```\n\n**Visual:**\n- Cyan to purple linear gradient\n- Pulsing scale animation (easeInOut 1.0s, repeating)\n- Cycles through 3 dot states\n\n---\n\n#### **E. ToolCallCardView** (`ChatPlugin.swift`, lines 1497-1607)\n\n```swift\nstruct ToolCallCardView: View {\n    let toolCall: ToolCall\n    @State private var isExpanded = false\n    \n    // Header (always visible):\n    //   └─ Chevron | Icon | ToolName | StatusBadge | Args preview\n    // Expanded:\n    //   └─ Arguments section (monospaced, secondary)\n    //   └─ Result section (truncated to 20 lines, monospaced)\n}\n```\n\n**Status badge:**\n- ✓ Green circle (completed)\n- ✗ Red circle (error)\n- ProgressView spinner (running)\n\n**Colors by status:**\n- Completed → green\n- Error → red\n- Running → orange\n\n---\n\n#### **F. UserQuestionCardView** (`ChatPlugin.swift`, lines 1731-1841)\n\nInteractive prompt with option buttons:\n\n```swift\nstruct UserQuestionCardView: View {\n    let question: UserQuestion\n    let onAnswer: (String) -> Void\n    \n    // Header: \"?\" icon + question text\n    // Options: Radio button list (selectable)\n    // Custom input: \"Other...\" expandable text field\n}\n```\n\n**Visual:**\n- Purple background (0.06 opacity)\n- Purple border (0.15 opacity), 0.75pt\n- Options are capsule buttons with selections\n- \"Other...\" expands to text field with \"Send\" button\n\n---\n\n#### **G. SessionStatusBar** (`ChatPlugin.swift`, lines 1208-1243)\n\nMetadata display below message list:\n\n```swift\nstruct SessionStatusBar: View {\n    let metadata: SessionMetadata\n    // Shows: Model | Token count | Duration | Cost\n    // Each as a capsule badge with icon + text\n}\n```\n\n**Metadata extraction** (`ChatPlugin.swift`, lines 310-355):\n- Scans last 10 lines of response for patterns:\n  - `Model: ...`\n  - `Tokens: ...` (parses integer, removes commas)\n  - `Duration: ...`\n  - `Cost: ...`\n  - `Session: ...` (skipped in display)\n- Removes metadata lines from content before storing\n- Returns `(cleanContent, metadata)` tuple\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Mini Chat Card (for floating notification)** (`SmartInputWindowManager.swift`, lines 676-824)\n\nFloats above the bubble when new assistant messages arrive:\n\n```swift\nprivate struct MiniChatCard: View {\n    let messages: [MiniChatMessage]\n    let onDismiss: () -> Void\n    \n    // Header: Logo | \"Orchestra\" | Copy button | Dismiss\n    // ScrollView: Full conversation with MiniChatBubble items\n    // Footer: Divider + scrollable message list\n}\n```\n\n**Layout:**\n- 700pt wide, 360pt tall\n- Glass background (`.ultraThinMaterial`)\n- Appears above the bubble with spring animation\n- Shows full session history\n- Copy button for last assistant message\n- 50pt dismiss zone on right edge\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Panel Transition & Animation** (`SmartInputWindowManager.swift`)\n\n#### **Bubble → Expanded**\n```swift\npublic func expand() {\n    // 1. Capture bubble position (right edge fixed)\n    // 2. Hide content (alphaValue = 0)\n    // 3. Swap to expanded card\n    // 4. Show with instant frame reset\n    // 5. Animate to expanded size over 0.30s (easeInEaseOut)\n    // 6. Restore alphaValue = 1\n}\n```\n\n**Key:** Right edge stays fixed; card grows leftward. Logo ends up at left.\n\n#### **Expanded → Bubble**\n```swift\npublic func collapse() {\n    // 1. Animate shrink back to bubble size (0.30s)\n    // 2. On animation complete:\n    //    - Set isExpanded = false\n    //    - Swap to bubble view\n    //    - Restore alphaValue = 1\n}\n```\n\n**Timing:** 30pt spring easing, mirrors expand animation.\n\n#### **Resize handling** (when toolbar changes height)\n```swift\npublic func resizeIfNeeded() {\n    // Instant frame change (NO NSAnimationContext)\n    // This prevents NSHostingView.updateAnimatedWindowSize crash\n    // during layout pass while SwiftUI animations are running\n}\n```\n\n**Critical:** No animated resize—avoids NSHostingView crash.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Content Display Architecture**\n\n#### **ChatDetailView** (main chat area)\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Session title | Model badge | Provider │ ← Header\n├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                         │\n│    MessageList (scrollable)             │ ← Chat history\n│    └─ ChatBubble (user/assistant)       │\n│                                         │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  [Permission Request View] (if pending) │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  DockedInputBar (if not detached)       │ ← Glass input bar\n├─────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  SessionStatusBar (if metadata)         │ ← Model/tokens/cost\n└─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n#### **SmartFloatingContent** (expanded card on bubble click)\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────┐\n│   InputBarContent                    │ ← Text field + actions\n│   (shared with DockedInputBar)       │\n└──────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n- Expands leftward from bubble\n- Uses `.ultraThinMaterial` glass background\n- Border: white.opacity(0.25), 0.75pt\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Message Sending Flow** (`ChatPlugin.swift`, lines 211-272)\n\n```\n1. User types + taps send\n2. Plugin.sendMessage(text)\n   ├─ Create ChatMessage(.user, content)\n   ├─ If no bridgeSessionId:\n   │  └─ create_session → get \"s-XXXXXX\"\n   ├─ Call bridge \"send_message\" tool\n   ├─ Extract metadata from tail\n   ├─ Parse tool calls (checkmark/X prefixes)\n   ├─ Parse AskUserQuestion (JSON or \"? ...\" format)\n   └─ Create ChatMessage(.assistant, content, toolCalls, question)\n```\n\n**Metadata extraction:**\n- Scans last 10 lines\n- Recognizes: Model:, Tokens:, Duration:, Cost:, Session:\n- Removes recognized lines before storing\n\n**Tool call parsing:**\n- Checkmark prefixes: ✓, ✔, ✅ → status.completed\n- Error prefixes: ✗, ✘, ❌ → status.error\n- Format: \"✓ Read file.swift args\" → toolName=\"Read\", arguments=\"file.swift args\"\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Styling & Theming**\n\n#### **Color Palette**\n- **Session colors**: red, orange, yellow, green, teal, blue, indigo, purple, pink, gray (user-selectable)\n- **Message backgrounds**:\n  - User: `.accentColor` (blue)\n  - Assistant: `.secondary.opacity(0.15)` (gray)\n- **Tool cards**: `.secondary.opacity(0.08)` with 0.5pt border\n- **Question cards**: `.purple.opacity(0.06)` background, purple border\n\n#### **Typography**\n- **Message text**: 13.5pt system\n- **Code**: 12pt monospaced, white 0.88 opacity\n- **Headings**: 20pt (H1) → 14pt (H6), semibold\n- **Tool name**: 12pt semibold monospaced\n- **Status badge**: 11pt system\n\n#### **Glass Effects**\n- `.ultraThinMaterial` for floating panels\n- Overlay: white.opacity(0.10) tint\n- Border: white.opacity(0.25) or white.opacity(0.12)\n- Shadow: black.opacity(0.15-0.20), radius 6pt\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Key Implementation Notes**\n\n1. **No streaming UI**: Messages are fully formed when added (streaming happens in Go bridge)\n2. **Markdown parsing**: Pure Swift, no regex, no network calls\n3. **Metadata extraction**: Regex-free string parsing from tail\n4. **Tool call UI**: Collapsible cards with status badges\n5. **Interactive questions**: Option buttons + custom text input\n6. **TTS**: macOS only, speaker button in assistant messages\n7. **Auto-scroll**: ScrollViewReader with onChange on message count\n8. **Panel animation**: 0.30s spring (easeInEaseOut), right edge fixed\n9. **Resize safety**: No NSAnimationContext on floating panel resize\n10. **Persistence**: JSON serialization to `~/Library/Application Support/Orchestra/chat-sessions.json`\n\n---\n\n### File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- **Models**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/OrchestraKit/Sources/OrchestraKit/Models/Models.swift`\n- **Chat Plugin**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Plugins/ChatPlugin/ChatPlugin.swift`\n- **Markdown renderer**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Components/MarkdownContentView.swift`\n- **Window manager**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift`\n- **Floating content**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Components/SmartFloatingContent.swift`\n- **Input bar**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Components/SmartInputBar.swift`\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive exploration covers all 6 areas you requested. The codebase is well-structured with clear separation between models, views, and window management. The chat message display is fully native SwiftUI with custom markdown parsing, and the floating bubble-to-expanded-card transition is smooth and memory-safe."
