        tool_response:
            agentId: a938107e6b32fc191
            content:
                - text: "Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Swift mini panel / floating panel architecture in the Orchestra macOS app. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n## 1. SmartInputWindowManager\n\n**File**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift`\n\n**Key Methods**:\n- `expand()` — Expands bubble to card (700×variable height), animates leftward\n- `collapse()` — Shrinks card back to 64×64 bubble\n- `togglePanel()` — Show/hide the entire floating panel\n- `showOnLaunch()` — Display bubble on app startup (tray-only mode)\n- `isPanelVisible` — Computed property: `panel != nil && (panel?.isVisible ?? false)`\n- `openPanel(chatPlugin:)` — Create panel and expand\n- `dismissPanel()` — Hide and destroy the panel\n- `dockToChat()` — Return to docked input bar in main window\n- `registerGlobalHotkey()` — Cmd+K hotkey for toggle\n- `removeGlobalHotkey()` — Clean up monitors\n\n**State**:\n- `@Published var isExpanded: Bool` — Drives SmartFloatingContent view state\n- `panel: TransparentPanel?` — NSPanel instance\n- `chatPlugin: ChatPlugin?` — Reference to chat system\n- `messagePollingTimer` — 0.5s timer that watches for new assistant messages and shows the floating mini-chat card\n\n**Message Polling** (lines 266–301):\n- Polls every 0.5 seconds when panel is created\n- Tracks last seen message count + session ID\n- When new assistant messages arrive and chat window is closed, calls `SiriResponseWindowManager.shared.showChat()`\n- This triggers the floating mini-chat card to appear above the bubble\n\n**Layout Calculations**:\n- `bubbleSize: 64pt`\n- `expandedWidth: 700pt`\n- `expandedHeight` dynamic: 60pt (input row) + 48pt (toolbar if visible) + trigger autocomplete rows\n\n**Drag Handling** (TransparentPanel sendEvent):\n- Bubble mode: whole panel is draggable\n- Expanded mode: logo zone (left edge 46pt) is draggable + tap-to-collapse; dock button zone (84pt total) is tappable\n\n**Position Persistence**:\n- Saved to UserDefaults: `smartInput.x`, `smartInput.y`\n- Default: bottom-right corner, validated to be on-screen\n\n---\n\n## 2. SmartFloatingContent\n\n**File**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Components/SmartFloatingContent.swift`\n\n**Structure**:\n```\nSmartFloatingContent\n├─ if expanded: expandedCard\n│  ├─ InputBarContent (isFloating: true)\n│  ├─ .ultraThinMaterial glass background\n│  ├─ RoundedRectangle 22pt radius\n│  └─ Overlay borders + shadow\n└─ else: bubbleButton\n   ├─ 64×64 Circle with logo\n   ├─ .ultraThinMaterial background\n   └─ Animated rotation on tap\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- Observes `manager.isExpanded` to switch view\n- Logo rotation animation on tap (0.7s smooth rotation)\n- Sends `.orchestraCollapseSmartInput` notification on logo tap (1/4 spin + collapse delay)\n- Delegates input logic to `InputBarContent(isFloating: true)`\n- Kills all SwiftUI animations via `.transaction { $0.disablesAnimations = true }` to prevent NSHostingView crashes\n- Notifies height changes via `.orchestraInputHeightChanged` when triggers activate/deactivate\n\n**Glass Styling**:\n- Background: `.ultraThinMaterial`\n- Tint: `Color.white.opacity(0.10)`\n- Border: `Color.white.opacity(0.25)`, 0.75pt\n- Shadow: `Color.black.opacity(0.15)`, radius 6, y: 3\n\n---\n\n## 3. InputBarContent\n\n**File**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Components/InputBarContent.swift`\n\n**Parameters**:\n- `chatPlugin: ChatPlugin?` — Reference to chat system\n- `sessionId: UUID?` — Explicit session (if nil, uses chatPlugin.selectedSession)\n- `isFloating: Bool` — True for NSPanel, false for docked bar\n- `onDock: (() -> Void)?` — Callback to dock floating panel\n- `onDetach: (() -> Void)?` — Callback to detach docked bar\n- `onHeightChange: (() -> Void)?` — Notify manager when height changes\n\n**Content Stack** (lines 98–119):\n```\nVStack {\n  ├─ File attachment chips (if any)\n  ├─ Input row (logo + dock button + text field + quick actions toggle)\n  ├─ Divider + quick actions row (if showQuickActions)\n  └─ InputToolbar (if trigger active)\n}\n```\n\n**Input Row** (lines 124–182):\n- Logo 26×26 (floating) or 24×24 (docked)\n- Dock/detach button (conditionally shown if not in tray mode)\n- Text field with voice mode overlay (ZStack + opacity trick to avoid tree swaps)\n- Hidden keyboard shortcuts (Enter, Cmd+Enter, Escape for floating, Cmd+V for paste)\n- Voice inline indicator when `voiceService.voiceModeActive`\n\n**Voice Inline Indicator** (lines 187–227):\n- Animated phase dot with audio level scaling\n- Phase label: \"Voice\", \"Listening...\", \"Thinking...\", \"Speaking...\"\n- Transcribed text (if listening)\n- Color codes: blue (idle/listening), purple (processing), green (speaking)\n\n**Send or Stop Button** (lines 234–277):\n- ZStack with three overlapping buttons (opacity trick):\n  1. **Voice stop button** (red, visible when voice active)\n  2. **Loading dots** (cyan→purple gradient, visible when `state.isLoading`)\n  3. **Send button** (white, visible when not voice/not loading)\n- Send button: arrow.up icon, disabled when text empty/already loading\n- Scale effect: 1.0 when enabled, 0.85 when disabled\n\n**Loading Dots Animation** (InputBarLoadingDots, lines 1070–1094):\n```swift\nHStack(spacing: 5) {\n  ForEach(0..<3, id: \\.self) { i in\n    Circle()\n      .fill(LinearGradient(cyan→purple))\n      .frame(6×6)\n      .opacity(phase == i ? 1.0 : 0.25)\n      .scaleEffect(phase == i ? 1.3 : 0.85)\n      .animation(.easeInOut(duration: 0.3), value: phase)\n  }\n}\n.onReceive(timer every: 0.38s) { _ in phase = (phase + 1) % 3 }\n```\nThree dots cycle through phases with 0.38s interval, each dot pulses (scale + opacity) for 0.3s when its phase is active.\n\n**Quick Actions Row** (lines 361–379):\n- Session model/mode/thinking buttons (chat-only)\n- Context button, suggestions, browser, screenshot buttons\n- Mic button\n- Send or stop button\n\n**Send Message Flow** (lines 723–780):\n```swift\nprivate func sendMessage() {\n  if state.isChatMode {\n    // Chat mode: delegate to ChatPlugin.sendMessage()\n    guard !prompt.isEmpty, let chat = state.activeChatPlugin else { return }\n    state.text = \"\"\n    Task { await chat.sendMessage(prompt) }\n  } else {\n    // Standalone mode: call ai_prompt tool directly\n    state.text = \"\"\n    state.isLoading = true\n    Task {\n      do {\n        let result = try await ToolService.shared.call(tool: \"ai_prompt\", arguments: [\n          \"prompt\": prompt,\n          \"wait\": true,\n          \"provider\": \"claude\",\n          \"system_prompt\": systemContext (optional)\n        ])\n        state.lastResponse = result\n        state.showingResponse = true\n        // Show mini-chat card if floating\n        if let mgr { SiriResponseWindowManager.shared.showMessages(...) }\n      } catch {\n        // Handle error\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nKey points:\n- File paths + browser context prepended to prompt\n- `state.isLoading = true` triggers loading dots animation\n- Non-chat mode calls `ai_prompt` tool with optional system context\n- Success shows response in floating mini-chat card (if floating) or inline response card (if docked)\n\n---\n\n## 4. TransparentPanel (NSPanel subclass)\n\n**File**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift` (lines 37–169)\n\n**Properties**:\n- `bubbleMode: Bool` — Switches between drag-whole-panel vs. logo-zone-only\n- `onDragStart: (() -> Void)?` — Called when drag begins (captures mini-chat card origin)\n- `onDrag: ((dx, dy) -> Void)?` — Called during drag with cumulative deltas (co-moves mini-chat card)\n\n**Bubble Mode Event Handling** (lines 58–86):\n- Left mouse down: Start drag, save origin\n- Left mouse dragged: Move 4pt+ threshold → drag panel, set closed-hand cursor\n- Left mouse up: Save position, reset cursor\n\n**Expanded Mode Event Handling** (lines 88–167):\n- **Logo zone** (left 46pt, excluding toolbar row):\n  - Mouse down: Track for drag\n  - Mouse dragged (4pt+ threshold): Move panel, cursor = closed-hand\n  - Mouse up: If dragged, save position; if pure tap, spin logo + collapse after 250ms\n- **Dock button zone** (46–84pt, excluding toolbar row):\n  - Mouse down: Track\n  - Mouse up: If pure tap (no drag), call `dockToChat()`\n- **Toolbar row** (bottom, if visible): Full pass-through for button clicks\n- **Rest of card**: Full pass-through to SwiftUI content\n\n**Panel Setup** (createPanelIfNeeded, lines 499–532):\n```swift\nlet p = TransparentPanel(\n  contentRect: bubbleRect,\n  styleMask: [.nonactivatingPanel, .borderless],\n  backing: .buffered,\n  defer: false\n)\np.level = .floating\np.isOpaque = false\np.backgroundColor = .clear\np.hasShadow = false\np.appearance = NSAppearance(named: .vibrantDark)\np.collectionBehavior = [.canJoinAllSpaces, .fullScreenAuxiliary]\np.isMovableByWindowBackground = false\np.bubbleMode = true\n```\n\n**Content Rendering** (refreshContent, lines 534–546):\n- Uses `ClearHostingView` (custom NSHostingView subclass)\n- Capsule mask: radius = min(width, height)/2 for bubble, 22pt for expanded card\n- Updates mask on layout/updateLayer to track resize animations\n- Dark appearance ensures `.ultraThinMaterial` renders as dark frosted glass\n\n---\n\n## 5. ChatPlugin\n\n**File**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Plugins/ChatPlugin/ChatPlugin.swift`\n\n**State**:\n- `@Published var sessions: [ChatSession]` — All conversations\n- `@Published var selectedSession: ChatSession?` — Current session\n- `@Published var isSending: Bool` — Whether waiting for response\n- `@Published var loadingWord: String` — Current loading verb (rotating)\n- `@Published var selectedIds: Set<UUID>` — For multi-select\n- `@Published var sessionMetadata: SessionMetadata?` — Session metadata from response\n\n**Loading Word Animation** (lines 540–565):\n```swift\nstatic let loadingWords: [String] = [\n  \"Thinking\", \"Pondering\", \"Brewing\", \"Conjuring\", \"Weaving\",\n  \"Crafting\", \"Dreaming\", \"Exploring\", \"Imagining\", \"Composing\",\n  \"Analyzing\", \"Processing\", \"Computing\", \"Decoding\", \"Synthesizing\"\n]\n\nprivate func startLoadingWordTimer() {\n  loadingWordIndex = 0\n  loadingWord = Self.loadingWords[0]\n  loadingWordTimer = Timer.scheduledTimer(withTimeInterval: 2.0, repeats: true) { [weak self] _ in\n    Task { @MainActor [weak self] in\n      self?.loadingWordIndex = (self?.loadingWordIndex ?? 0 + 1) % Self.loadingWords.count\n      self?.loadingWord = Self.loadingWords[self?.loadingWordIndex ?? 0]\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nprivate func stopLoadingWordTimer() {\n  loadingWordTimer?.invalidate()\n  loadingWordTimer = nil\n  loadingWord = \"Thinking\"\n}\n```\nCycles through 15 loading words every 2 seconds while isSending is true. Updates observed by TypingIndicator in MessageList.\n\n**Send Message Flow** (lines 211–272):\n```swift\npublic func sendMessage(_ text: String) async {\n  guard var session = selectedSession else { return }\n  \n  let userMsg = ChatMessage(sessionId: session.id, role: .user, content: text)\n  append(userMsg, to: &session)\n  \n  isSending = true\n  defer { isSending = false }\n  \n  do {\n    // Ensure bridge session exists (create if first message)\n    if session.bridgeSessionId == nil {\n      let bridgeId = try await createBridgeSession(for: session)\n      session.bridgeSessionId = bridgeId\n      // Persist + notify\n    }\n    \n    // Prepend thinking instruction if enabled\n    var messageText = text\n    if session.thinkingEnabled {\n      messageText = \"Think step by step...\\n\\n\\(messageText)\"\n    }\n    \n    // Call tools-sessions plugin: send_message tool\n    let result = try await ToolService.shared.call(\n      tool: \"send_message\",\n      arguments: [\"session_id\": bridgeId, \"message\": messageText]\n    )\n    \n    // Extract metadata from response tail\n    let (cleanContent, metadata) = Self.extractMetadata(from: result)\n    if metadata.hasData { sessionMetadata = metadata }\n    \n    // Parse tool calls + user questions\n    let toolCalls = Self.parseToolCalls(from: cleanContent)\n    let pendingQuestion = Self.parseUserQuestion(from: cleanContent)\n    \n    let assistantMsg = ChatMessage(\n      sessionId: session.id,\n      role: .assistant,\n      content: cleanContent,\n      toolCalls: toolCalls,\n      pendingQuestion: pendingQuestion\n    )\n    append(assistantMsg, to: &session)\n  } catch {\n    // Append error message\n  }\n}\n```\n\nKey points:\n- Sets `isSending = true`, triggering loading word timer\n- Creates bridge session on first message (via `send_message` tool from tools-sessions plugin)\n- Calls `send_message` tool with session ID + message text\n- Extracts metadata, tool calls, user questions from response\n- Appends assistant message to session\n- `defer { isSending = false }` stops loading word timer\n\n---\n\n## 6. Message Display & Typing Indicator\n\n**MessageList** (lines 1329–1366):\n```swift\nstruct MessageList: View {\n  let session: ChatSession\n  var isSending: Bool = false\n  var loadingWord: String = \"Thinking\"\n  \n  var body: some View {\n    ScrollViewReader { proxy in\n      ScrollView {\n        LazyVStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: 8) {\n          ForEach(session.messages) { message in\n            ChatBubble(message: message, onQuestionAnswer: ...)\n              .id(message.id)\n          }\n          if isSending {\n            TypingIndicator(loadingWord: loadingWord)  // <-- Typing indicator\n              .id(\"typing-indicator\")\n          }\n        }\n      }\n      .onChange(of: session.messages.count) { _, _ in\n        withAnimation(.easeOut(duration: 0.2)) {\n          proxy.scrollTo(last.id, anchor: .bottom)\n        }\n      }\n      .onChange(of: isSending) { _, sending in\n        if sending {\n          withAnimation(.easeOut(duration: 0.2)) {\n            proxy.scrollTo(\"typing-indicator\", anchor: .bottom)\n          }\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**TypingIndicator** (lines 1370–1405):\n```swift\nprivate struct TypingIndicator: View {\n  var loadingWord: String = \"Thinking\"\n  @State private var dotPhase = 0\n  @State private var pulseScale: CGFloat = 1.0\n  private let timer = Timer.publish(every: 0.5, on: .main, in: .common).autoconnect()\n  \n  private let gradientColors: [Color] = [\n    Color(red: 0.00, green: 0.90, blue: 1.00),  // Cyan\n    Color(red: 0.66, green: 0.00, blue: 1.00),  // Purple\n  ]\n  \n  var body: some View {\n    HStack(alignment: .bottom, spacing: 0) {\n      HStack(spacing: 4) {\n        Text(loadingWord + String(repeating: \".\", count: dotPhase + 1))\n          .font(.system(size: 13, weight: .medium))\n          .foregroundStyle(\n            LinearGradient(\n              colors: gradientColors,\n              startPoint: .leading,\n              endPoint: .trailing\n            )\n          )\n          .scaleEffect(pulseScale)\n          .animation(.easeInOut(duration: 1.0).repeatForever(autoreverses: true), value: pulseScale)\n      }\n      .padding(.horizontal, 14)\n      .padding(.vertical, 10)\n      .background(Color.secondary.opacity(0.15))\n      .clipShape(RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 16, style: .continuous))\n      Spacer(minLength: 48)\n    }\n    .onReceive(timer) { _ in dotPhase = (dotPhase + 1) % 3 }\n    .onAppear { pulseScale = 1.03 }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAnimation breakdown:\n- **Dot cycling**: Every 0.5s, cycle through 0, 1, 2 dots (1–3 total dots)\n- **Pulse scaling**: 1.0 → 1.03 → 1.0 over 1.0s, repeats forever, autoreverses\n- **Gradient text**: Cyan→purple, left→right direction\n- **Loading word**: Updates every 2s from ChatPlugin.loadingWord\n- **Bubble styling**: Secondary color @ 15% opacity, 16pt radius\n- **Auto-scroll**: MessageList scrolls to typing indicator when isSending becomes true\n\n---\n\n## 7. Mini-Chat Card (SiriResponseWindowManager)\n\n**File**: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift` (lines 584–824)\n\n**Purpose**: Floating card that appears above the bubble when a response is received while chat is minimized.\n\n**Structure**:\n- 700×360pt, positioned above the bubble\n- Header: Logo + \"Orchestra\" + Copy button + Dismiss button\n- Divider\n- Scrollable full chat session (user bubbles in blue/accent color, assistant bubbles in white @ 8% opacity with markdown rendering)\n\n**Copy Button**: Copies last assistant response to pasteboard\n**Dismiss Button**: Fades out the card (right-edge 50pt zone is intercepted by ClickablePanel)\n\n**MiniChatCard View** (lines 681–792):\n- Scale animation on appear: 0.92 → 1.0\n- Uses `.ultraThinMaterial` glass background\n- Markdown rendering for assistant messages via `MarkdownContentView`\n- Auto-scrolls to last message on appear\n\n---\n\n## Key Architecture Insights\n\n1. **No streaming** — Messages are fully received before displaying. The `send_message` tool from tools-sessions plugin waits for the full response (`wait: true`).\n\n2. **Loading indicators**:\n   - **TypingIndicator** — Shows while `isSending == true`, with animated dots + rotating loading words\n   - **InputBarLoadingDots** — Three gradient dots pulsing in sequence while loading\n\n3. **Floating panel lifecycle**:\n   - Bubble (64×64) → tap → logo animation → expand\n   - Expanded → tap logo → spin animation → collapse\n   - Keyboard Cmd+K → togglePanel\n   - Dock button → dockToChat (returns to main window input bar)\n\n4. **Message polling** — SmartInputWindowManager polls every 0.5s for new assistant messages. When detected (and chat window is closed), shows the mini-chat card above the bubble.\n\n5. **View stability** — Uses ZStack + opacity tricks extensively (not if/else) to avoid NSHostingView crashes when the floating panel resizes during animations.\n\n6. **Glass styling** — `.ultraThinMaterial` on dark appearance (NSAppearance.vibrantDark) renders as frosted glass. All overlays use white @ variable opacity for depth.\n\n7. **Context injection** — Smart input bar can prepend browser context, file paths, and system context to prompts automatically.\n\n---\n\n## Files Summary\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| SmartInputWindowManager.swift | Floating panel lifecycle, positioning, drag handling, message polling |\n| SmartFloatingContent.swift | Bubble vs. expanded card view switcher |\n| InputBarContent.swift | Unified input bar (docked + floating), send logic, file/context/voice UI |\n| ChatPlugin.swift | Chat state, session management, message sending, loading word animation, typing indicator |\n| TransparentPanel (in SmartInputWindowManager.swift) | NSPanel subclass with custom drag/click handling |\n| SiriResponseWindowManager (in SmartInputWindowManager.swift) | Floating mini-chat card for background notifications |\n\nAll absolute file paths are in `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/`."
                  type: text
