        hook_event_name: SubagentStop
        last_assistant_message: "<analysis>\nLet me chronologically analyze the conversation:\n\n1. **First context**: The conversation was continued from a previous session. The summary tells us:\n   - Request 1 (COMPLETED): Remove all old versions/tags and release v1.0.0 of Orchestra framework\n   - Request 2 (IN PROGRESS): Add Windows/Git Bash support to Orchestra CLI\n   - Several Go files were already modified for Windows support (install.sh, install.go, pluginloader.go, selfupdate.go)\n   - Remaining: serve.go, pack.go, ide.go, release.yml, Makefile, add-plugin-release-workflow.sh, build verification\n\n2. **My first actions in this session**: Continued implementing Windows support\n   - Read serve.go, pack.go, ide.go in parallel\n   - Edited serve.go: Added `runtime` import, conditional signal handling (`os.Interrupt` on Windows vs `syscall.SIGINT/SIGTERM` on Unix)\n   - Edited pack.go: Added `runtime` import, guarded `os.Chmod` with `runtime.GOOS != \"windows\"`\n   - Edited ide.go: Added `runtime` import, normalized Continue.dev YAML paths with `filepath.ToSlash()` on Windows\n   - Read release.yml, Makefile, add-plugin-release-workflow.sh in parallel\n   - Edited release.yml: Added windows/amd64 matrix entry, `.exe` handling in Python build/package scripts\n   - Edited Makefile: Added Windows amd64 build loop with `.exe` binary names\n   - Edited add-plugin-release-workflow.sh: Added windows/amd64 matrix, `.exe` handling in build/package steps\n   - Verification: `make build-cli` passed, `GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64` cross-compile produced valid 18MB PE32+ executable, all tests passed\n\n3. **User request: \"release the framework v1.0.0 again\"**\n   - Deleted v1.0.0 tag/release from framework repo\n   - Deleted v1.0.0 tags/releases from all 45 repos (framework + 44 sub-repos)\n   - Committed framework-level Windows changes\n   - Ran `ship.sh v1.0.0 --skip-pr` — built, tested, bumped go.mod, synced CLI repo (only one with changes), tagged 42 repos, created framework release\n   - 2 repos skipped (plugin-transport-webtransport and plugin-tools-notes already had v1.0.0)\n\n4. **User reported CI error**: `build-sync-cloud` failed because `libs/plugin-sync-cloud` isn't in `orchestra.lock` (no GitHub repo exists)\n   - Fixed: Removed `build-sync-cloud` from Makefile's `build` target\n   - Re-tagged v1.0.0 from fixed commit\n\n5. **User reported Windows curl error**: `CRYPT_E_NO_REVOCATION_CHECK` (Schannel TLS revocation check failure)\n   - Fixed: Added `CURL_EXTRA=\"--ssl-revoke-best-effort\"` variable in install.sh, applied to all curl calls on Windows\n   - Re-tagged v1.0.0 again\n\n6. **User reported Windows PATH issue**: \"how to do this on windows?\"\n   - Updated install.sh to print PowerShell command for adding to PATH on Windows\n   - Re-tagged v1.0.0\n\n7. **User request: \"update README.md file with the last update for framework and push it\"**\n   - Rewrote README.md to reflect v1.0.0 state: 290 tools, 36 plugins, Windows support, in-process architecture, all 44 packages\n   - Pushed to master\n\n8. **User request: \"link git repos into the README.md file for plugins and packs\"**\n   - This is the CURRENT/PENDING task — add GitHub repo links to the plugin and pack tables in README.md\n\nLet me now document all the specific files and changes.\n</analysis>\n\n<summary>\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The conversation spans multiple sequential requests:\n   \n   **Request 1 (COMPLETED in prior session)**: Remove all old versions/tags from all Orchestra repos and release v1.0.0.\n   \n   **Request 2 (COMPLETED)**: Add Windows/Git Bash support to Orchestra. Modified 10 files across Go CLI, CI/CD, and install scripts.\n   \n   **Request 3 (COMPLETED)**: \"release the framework v1.0.0 again\" — Re-release v1.0.0 with all Windows support changes included. Required nuking v1.0.0 from all 45 repos and re-running ship.sh.\n   \n   **Request 4 (COMPLETED)**: Fix CI error — `build-sync-cloud` failing because plugin-sync-cloud isn't in orchestra.lock.\n   \n   **Request 5 (COMPLETED)**: Fix Windows curl TLS error — `CRYPT_E_NO_REVOCATION_CHECK` (Schannel revocation check failure).\n   \n   **Request 6 (COMPLETED)**: Show Windows PATH instructions in install script output.\n   \n   **Request 7 (COMPLETED)**: \"update README.md file with the last update for framework and push it\" — Full README rewrite for v1.0.0.\n   \n   **Request 8 (PENDING)**: \"link git repos into the README.md file for plugins and packs\" — Add clickable GitHub links to plugin and pack tables in README.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - **Orchestra Framework**: AI-agentic IDE framework, 290 MCP tools, 36 plugins, 44 Go module packages\n   - **In-process architecture**: 4 core plugins bundled (storage.markdown, tools.features, tools.marketplace, transport.stdio), 32 optional via QUIC\n   - **Windows/Git Bash support**: MINGW/MSYS detection, `.exe` binary suffix, guarded `os.Chmod`, `os.Interrupt` signal handling, `filepath.ToSlash()` for YAML paths\n   - **Cross-compilation**: `GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64` produces PE32+ executables from macOS\n   - **ship.sh pipeline**: build → test → bump go.mod → commit → push → sync sub-repos → tag/release all 44 repos → framework tag\n   - **orchestra.lock**: JSON lockfile listing all 44 packages with versions, paths, git URLs — used by CI to clone dependencies\n   - **go.work**: Local workspace file, CI regenerates from orchestra.lock (so local-only modules like sync-cloud don't break CI)\n   - **Schannel TLS**: Windows native TLS backend that fails on certificate revocation checks behind firewalls; fix is `--ssl-revoke-best-effort`\n   - **GitHub org**: `orchestra-mcp/*` — 44 sub-repos + framework repo\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`scripts/install.sh`** (modified 3 times)\n     - Windows platform detection, `.exe` handling, skip chmod/sudo, default install dir\n     - `CURL_EXTRA=\"--ssl-revoke-best-effort\"` for Windows Schannel TLS fix\n     - PowerShell PATH instructions for Windows users\n     - Current state includes all three fixes\n\n   - **`libs/cli/internal/install.go`** (modified in prior session)\n     - Added `binaryExt()` helper returning `.exe` on Windows\n     - Guarded chmod, fixed extractTarGz binary matching\n\n   - **`libs/cli/internal/pluginloader.go`** (modified in prior session)\n     - Appends `.exe` to plugin binary path on Windows\n\n   - **`libs/cli/internal/selfupdate.go`** (modified in prior session)\n     - Uses `binaryExt()` for update loop + extractTarGzAll, guarded chmod\n\n   - **`libs/cli/internal/serve.go`** (modified)\n     - Added `\"runtime\"` import\n     - Signal handling: `os.Interrupt` on Windows vs `syscall.SIGINT/SIGTERM` on Unix\n     ```go\n     if runtime.GOOS == \"windows\" {\n         signal.Notify(sigCh, os.Interrupt)\n     } else {\n         signal.Notify(sigCh, syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM)\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`libs/cli/internal/pack.go`** (modified)\n     - Added `\"runtime\"` import\n     - Guarded chmod on hook files:\n     ```go\n     if runtime.GOOS != \"windows\" {\n         os.Chmod(dst, 0755)\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`libs/cli/internal/ide.go`** (modified)\n     - Added `\"runtime\"` import\n     - Continue.dev YAML path normalization:\n     ```go\n     if runtime.GOOS == \"windows\" {\n         yamlBin = filepath.ToSlash(bin)\n         yamlWs = filepath.ToSlash(ws)\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`.github/workflows/release.yml`** (modified)\n     - Added `windows/amd64` matrix entry with `runner: windows-latest`\n     - Python build script: `ext = \".exe\" if goos == \"windows\" else \"\"`\n     - Package step: adds `.exe` suffix to binary list on Windows\n\n   - **`Makefile`** (modified twice)\n     - Added Windows amd64 build loop with `.exe` binary names for release target\n     - Removed `build-sync-cloud` from `build` target (plugin-sync-cloud not in orchestra.lock)\n\n   - **`scripts/add-plugin-release-workflow.sh`** (modified)\n     - Added `windows/amd64` matrix entry\n     - Build/package steps handle `.exe` extension via shell conditional\n\n   - **`README.md`** (rewritten)\n     - Updated for v1.0.0: 290 tools, 36 plugins, Windows support, in-process architecture\n     - Added Windows install command, plugin table by category, updated architecture diagram\n     - All 44 module paths listed\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **CI `build-sync-cloud` failure**: `libs/plugin-sync-cloud` exists locally but has no GitHub repo and isn't in `orchestra.lock`, so CI can't clone it. The Makefile's `build` target included `build-sync-cloud`.\n     - Fix: Removed `build-sync-cloud` from the `build` dependency list in Makefile\n     - Re-tagged v1.0.0 from the fixed commit\n   \n   - **Windows curl TLS error**: `CRYPT_E_NO_REVOCATION_CHECK (0x80092012)` — Windows Schannel backend fails certificate revocation checks behind corporate firewalls/proxies.\n     - Fix: Added `CURL_EXTRA=\"--ssl-revoke-best-effort\"` variable set only on Windows (MINGW/MSYS/CYGWIN), applied to all curl calls in install.sh\n   \n   - **Windows PATH not set**: After install, `orchestra` not found in PATH. User asked \"how to do this on windows?\"\n     - Fix: Updated install.sh to print PowerShell command: `[Environment]::SetEnvironmentVariable('Path', ... + ';${INSTALL_DIR}', 'User')`\n   \n   - **v1.0.0 re-tagging**: Had to delete and recreate v1.0.0 tag/release 3 times as fixes were applied (build-sync-cloud fix, curl fix, PATH instructions). Each time: `gh release delete` → `gh api -X DELETE refs/tags` → `git tag -d` → `git tag` → `git push origin` → `gh release create`.\n\n   - **2 repos skipped during release**: `plugin-transport-webtransport` and `plugin-tools-notes` already had v1.0.0 tags from incomplete previous nuke. Not a blocking issue.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Windows support required changes across 10 files spanning Go code, shell scripts, CI workflows, and Makefile\n   - The `build-sync-cloud` issue highlighted the gap between local dev (go.work includes sync-cloud) and CI (uses orchestra.lock which doesn't)\n   - Windows curl TLS is a known issue with Schannel; `--ssl-revoke-best-effort` is the standard workaround\n   - v1.0.0 was re-released 3 times to incorporate incremental fixes discovered through real user testing on Windows\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - (Continuation from prior session with Windows support implementation in progress)\n   - \"release the framework v1.0.0 again\"\n   - CI error report: `build-sync-cloud` failing with \"cd: can't cd to libs/plugin-sync-cloud\" — \"check the error for workflow make sure it's all done\"\n   - Windows curl error: \"when some one install got this 'curl: (35) schannel: next InitializeSecurityContext failed: CRYPT_E_NO_REVOCATION_CHECK (0x80092012)'\"\n   - \"Note: Add C:\\Users\\Fr3on\\AppData\\Local/Orchestra/bin to your PATH if not already there. how to do this on windows?\"\n   - \"update README.md file with the last update for framework and push it\"\n   - \"link git repos into the README.md file for plugins and packs\"\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - **Add GitHub repo links to README.md**: User's latest request — \"link git repos into the README.md file for plugins and packs\". Need to add clickable links to plugin names and pack names in the README tables, linking to their respective GitHub repos under `github.com/orchestra-mcp/`.\n\n8. Current Work:\n   The README was just rewritten and pushed. The user's most recent request is to add GitHub repository links into the README.md for plugins and packs. The plugin repos follow the pattern `github.com/orchestra-mcp/plugin-*` and pack repos follow `github.com/orchestra-mcp/pack-*`.\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Edit README.md to convert plugin names and pack names in the tables to markdown links pointing to their GitHub repositories. For example:\n   - `storage.markdown` → `[storage.markdown](https://github.com/orchestra-mcp/plugin-storage-markdown)`\n   - `pack-essentials` → `[pack-essentials](https://github.com/orchestra-mcp/pack-essentials)`\n   \n   The user's exact request: \"link git repos into the README.md file for plugins and packs\"\n</summary>"
        permission_mode: acceptEdits
