        last_assistant_message: "I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me produce the detailed implementation plan.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan: Mini Panel Improvements\n\nThis plan covers four features: (1) instant message display on send, (2) typewriter/streaming effect for AI responses, (3) status bar with agent ops metadata on the mini panel, and (4) a toggle button in the toolbar to show/hide the mini panel. Each is analyzed below with specific file changes, method signatures, and view structures.\n\n---\n\n### Overview of Current Architecture\n\nThe mini panel is managed by `SiriResponseWindowManager` (inside `SmartInputWindowManager.swift`). It creates a `ClickablePanel` (NSPanel subclass) containing a `MiniChatCard` SwiftUI view. Currently, the mini panel only appears after a full response arrives -- the 0.5s polling timer in `SmartInputWindowManager.pollMessages()` checks for new assistant messages and calls `SiriResponseWindowManager.shared.showChat(session:bubbleManager:)`.\n\nThe send flow is: `InputBarContent.sendMessage()` calls `ChatPlugin.sendMessage()`, which calls `ToolService.shared.call(tool: \"send_message\", ...)`. This blocks until the full response returns. Only then does the assistant message get appended, which the polling timer detects.\n\n---\n\n### Feature 1: Instant Message Display\n\n**Goal**: When the user presses send, immediately show the mini panel with their message and a loading indicator, before the AI response arrives.\n\n**Current problem**: `SiriResponseWindowManager.showChat()` requires at least one assistant message (line 599: `guard messages.contains(where: { $0.role == .assistant }) else { return }`). The mini panel only appears after polling detects a new assistant message count.\n\n**Changes**:\n\n#### File: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift`\n\n1. **`SiriResponseWindowManager.showChat()`** -- Remove the guard that requires an assistant message. Instead, allow showing user-only messages with a loading indicator:\n\n```swift\n// CURRENT (line 599):\nguard messages.contains(where: { $0.role == .assistant }) else { return }\n\n// NEW: Remove this guard entirely. The MiniChatCard will handle \n// displaying a loading state when no assistant message is present.\n```\n\n2. **Add a new method `showPendingChat()`** on `SiriResponseWindowManager` to be called immediately when the user sends a message:\n\n```swift\n/// Shows the mini panel immediately with the user's message and a loading indicator.\n/// Called by InputBarContent/ChatPlugin right after send, before the AI responds.\nfunc showPendingChat(userMessage: String, session: ChatSession, bubbleManager: SmartInputWindowManager) {\n    let messages = [MiniChatMessage(role: .user, content: userMessage)]\n    showMessages(messages, bubbleManager: bubbleManager, isLoading: true)\n}\n```\n\n3. **Modify `showMessages()`** to accept an `isLoading` parameter:\n\n```swift\nfunc showMessages(_ messages: [MiniChatMessage], bubbleManager: SmartInputWindowManager, isLoading: Bool = false) {\n    // ... existing code ...\n    createOrUpdate(messages: messages, bubbleManager: bubbleManager, isLoading: isLoading)\n}\n```\n\n4. **Modify `createOrUpdate()`** to pass `isLoading` to the view:\n\n```swift\nprivate func createOrUpdate(messages: [MiniChatMessage], bubbleManager: SmartInputWindowManager, isLoading: Bool = false) {\n    // ... existing panel setup ...\n    let hosting = NSHostingView(rootView: MiniChatCard(messages: messages, isLoading: isLoading) {\n        SiriResponseWindowManager.shared.dismiss()\n    })\n    // ... rest unchanged ...\n}\n```\n\n5. **Add `isLoading` property** to `SiriResponseWindowManager` so `pollMessages()` can update it:\n\n```swift\nprivate(set) var isLoading: Bool = false\n```\n\n#### File: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift` (MiniChatCard view)\n\n6. **Add `isLoading` parameter** to `MiniChatCard`:\n\n```swift\nprivate struct MiniChatCard: View {\n    let messages: [MiniChatMessage]\n    let isLoading: Bool        // NEW\n    let onDismiss: () -> Void\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n7. **Add a MiniTypingIndicator** at the bottom of the message list when `isLoading` is true (reuse the same animated gradient style from the main `TypingIndicator`):\n\n```swift\n// Inside MiniChatCard body, after ForEach(messages...)\nif isLoading {\n    MiniTypingIndicator()\n        .id(\"mini-typing\")\n}\n```\n\nThe `MiniTypingIndicator` should be a small version of the existing `TypingIndicator` -- same gradient animation style but scaled for the mini panel (smaller font, 11pt):\n\n```swift\nprivate struct MiniTypingIndicator: View {\n    @State private var dotPhase = 0\n    private let timer = Timer.publish(every: 0.5, on: .main, in: .common).autoconnect()\n    \n    var body: some View {\n        HStack(alignment: .bottom, spacing: 0) {\n            Text(\"Thinking\" + String(repeating: \".\", count: dotPhase + 1))\n                .font(.system(size: 11, weight: .medium))\n                .foregroundStyle(/* same gradient as TypingIndicator */)\n                .padding(.horizontal, 10)\n                .padding(.vertical, 6)\n                .background(Color.white.opacity(0.08))\n                .clipShape(RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: 12, style: .continuous))\n            Spacer(minLength: 40)\n        }\n        .onReceive(timer) { _ in dotPhase = (dotPhase + 1) % 3 }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### File: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Components/InputBarContent.swift`\n\n8. **In `sendMessage()`, immediately show the mini panel** when in chat mode (the `if state.isChatMode` branch, around line 724):\n\n```swift\n// After clearing text (line 735: state.text = \"\"), before Task { await chat.sendMessage(prompt) }:\n// Immediately show the mini panel with the user's message + loading\nif isFloating, let mgr = SmartInputWindowManager.shared as SmartInputWindowManager? {\n    SiriResponseWindowManager.shared.showPendingChat(\n        userMessage: prompt,\n        session: chat.selectedSession ?? ChatSession(title: \"Chat\"),\n        bubbleManager: mgr\n    )\n}\n```\n\n#### File: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift` (pollMessages)\n\n9. **Modify `pollMessages()`** -- When an assistant message arrives, update the mini panel (it is already visible from the instant show). The existing flow already calls `SiriResponseWindowManager.shared.showChat()`, which will now pass `isLoading: false` and show the full conversation. No major change needed here other than ensuring it passes `isLoading: false` explicitly.\n\n---\n\n### Feature 2: Typewriter/Streaming Effect\n\n**Goal**: Show the AI response character by character with a typewriter animation, like ChatGPT.\n\n**Approach**: Option C from the requirements -- fake streaming. The full response arrives at once via `send_message`, then we reveal it progressively. This avoids any backend changes and works with the existing infrastructure.\n\n#### File: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift`\n\n1. **Add a `TypewriterState` observable class** (or integrate into `SiriResponseWindowManager`):\n\n```swift\n@MainActor\nfinal class TypewriterState: ObservableObject {\n    @Published var displayedText: String = \"\"\n    @Published var isAnimating: Bool = false\n    \n    private var fullText: String = \"\"\n    private var currentIndex: String.Index?\n    private var timer: Timer?\n    \n    /// Characters per second for the typewriter effect\n    private let charsPerTick: Int = 3\n    private let tickInterval: TimeInterval = 0.016  // ~60fps, 3 chars per tick = ~180 chars/sec\n    \n    func startTypewriter(fullText: String) {\n        self.fullText = fullText\n        self.displayedText = \"\"\n        self.currentIndex = fullText.startIndex\n        self.isAnimating = true\n        \n        timer?.invalidate()\n        timer = Timer.scheduledTimer(withTimeInterval: tickInterval, repeats: true) { [weak self] _ in\n            Task { @MainActor [weak self] in\n                self?.advanceTypewriter()\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    func skipToEnd() {\n        timer?.invalidate()\n        timer = nil\n        displayedText = fullText\n        isAnimating = false\n    }\n    \n    private func advanceTypewriter() {\n        guard var idx = currentIndex, idx < fullText.endIndex else {\n            timer?.invalidate()\n            timer = nil\n            isAnimating = false\n            return\n        }\n        \n        // Advance by charsPerTick characters\n        for _ in 0..<charsPerTick {\n            guard idx < fullText.endIndex else { break }\n            idx = fullText.index(after: idx)\n        }\n        \n        currentIndex = idx\n        displayedText = String(fullText[fullText.startIndex..<idx])\n    }\n}\n```\n\n2. **Store a `TypewriterState` instance** on `SiriResponseWindowManager`:\n\n```swift\nlet typewriterState = TypewriterState()\n```\n\n3. **Modify the poll flow**: When `pollMessages()` detects a new assistant message, instead of immediately showing the full text, trigger the typewriter:\n\n```swift\n// In pollMessages(), after detecting newCount > lastSeenMessageCount:\nlastSeenMessageCount = newCount\n\nlet chatIsOpen = SmartInputState.shared.activeChatPlugin != nil\nguard !chatIsOpen else { return }\n\n// Get messages for display\nlet messages = session.messages\n    .filter { $0.role != .system }\n    .map { MiniChatMessage(role: $0.role == .user ? .user : .assistant, content: $0.content) }\n\n// Start typewriter for the latest assistant message\nif let lastAssistant = messages.last, lastAssistant.role == .assistant {\n    SiriResponseWindowManager.shared.showChatWithTypewriter(\n        messages: messages,\n        bubbleManager: self\n    )\n}\n```\n\n4. **Add `showChatWithTypewriter()`** on `SiriResponseWindowManager`:\n\n```swift\nfunc showChatWithTypewriter(messages: [MiniChatMessage], bubbleManager: SmartInputWindowManager) {\n    // Show all messages except the last assistant's full text\n    var displayMessages = messages\n    if let lastIdx = displayMessages.lastIndex(where: { $0.role == .assistant }) {\n        let fullText = displayMessages[lastIdx].content\n        displayMessages[lastIdx] = MiniChatMessage(role: .assistant, content: \"\")\n        typewriterState.startTypewriter(fullText: fullText)\n    }\n    isLoading = false\n    createOrUpdate(messages: displayMessages, bubbleManager: bubbleManager, isLoading: false)\n}\n```\n\n#### File: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift` (MiniChatCard)\n\n5. **In `MiniChatCard`, observe the `TypewriterState`** for the last assistant bubble:\n\n```swift\nprivate struct MiniChatCard: View {\n    let messages: [MiniChatMessage]\n    let isLoading: Bool\n    let onDismiss: () -> Void\n    @ObservedObject var typewriterState: TypewriterState  // NEW -- passed from SiriResponseWindowManager\n    \n    // In the body, the last assistant message uses typewriterState.displayedText\n    // instead of message.content when typewriterState.isAnimating\n}\n```\n\n6. **In the `MiniChatBubble` for the last assistant message**, swap the content:\n\n```swift\n// For the last assistant message in the ForEach:\nForEach(Array(messages.enumerated()), id: \\.offset) { i, msg in\n    if msg.role == .assistant && i == messages.lastIndex(where: { $0.role == .assistant }) && typewriterState.isAnimating {\n        MiniChatBubble(message: MiniChatMessage(\n            role: .assistant,\n            content: typewriterState.displayedText\n        ))\n        .id(i)\n    } else {\n        MiniChatBubble(message: msg).id(i)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n7. **Add a \"Skip\" button** that appears during typewriter animation (small, in the header bar next to Copy):\n\n```swift\nif typewriterState.isAnimating {\n    Button {\n        typewriterState.skipToEnd()\n    } label: {\n        HStack(spacing: 4) {\n            Image(systemName: \"forward.fill\")\n                .font(.system(size: 10, weight: .medium))\n            Text(\"Skip\")\n                .font(.system(size: 11, weight: .medium))\n        }\n        .foregroundStyle(.white.opacity(0.55))\n        .padding(.horizontal, 8)\n        .padding(.vertical, 4)\n        .background(.ultraThinMaterial, in: Capsule())\n    }\n    .buttonStyle(.plain)\n}\n```\n\n**Speed tuning**: At 3 characters per 16ms tick, that is approximately 180 characters per second. A typical 500-character response would take about 2.8 seconds. For longer responses, the speed could ramp up after the first 200 characters (double the charsPerTick to 6 once past the initial portion), giving a natural \"accelerating\" feel. This is configurable in `TypewriterState`.\n\n---\n\n### Feature 3: Status Bar on Mini Panel\n\n**Goal**: Show agent ops metadata (model, tokens, duration, cost) in a status bar on the mini panel.\n\n**Current state**: `SessionStatusBar` already exists in `ChatPlugin.swift` (line 1208) and renders nicely as capsule badges. It is used in `ChatDetailView` (line 1310-1312). The mini panel has no status bar.\n\n#### File: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift` (MiniChatCard)\n\n1. **Add metadata to MiniChatCard**:\n\n```swift\nprivate struct MiniChatCard: View {\n    let messages: [MiniChatMessage]\n    let isLoading: Bool\n    let metadata: SessionMetadata?   // NEW\n    let onDismiss: () -> Void\n    @ObservedObject var typewriterState: TypewriterState\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n2. **Add a `MiniStatusBar` view** at the bottom of the MiniChatCard, between the scrollable messages and the bottom edge. This should be a condensed version of `SessionStatusBar`:\n\n```swift\n// In MiniChatCard body, after the ScrollViewReader:\n\n// Status bar — shown when metadata is available and not loading\nif let meta = metadata, meta.hasData, !isLoading {\n    Rectangle()\n        .fill(Color.white.opacity(0.10))\n        .frame(height: 0.5)\n        .padding(.horizontal, 12)\n    \n    MiniStatusBar(metadata: meta)\n        .padding(.horizontal, 14)\n        .padding(.vertical, 6)\n}\n```\n\n3. **`MiniStatusBar` view** -- a compact version of `SessionStatusBar` styled for the mini panel:\n\n```swift\nprivate struct MiniStatusBar: View {\n    let metadata: SessionMetadata\n    \n    var body: some View {\n        HStack(spacing: 8) {\n            if !metadata.model.isEmpty {\n                miniMetaItem(icon: \"cpu\", text: metadata.model)\n            }\n            if metadata.tokenCount > 0 {\n                miniMetaItem(icon: \"number\", text: \"\\(metadata.tokenCount)\")\n            }\n            if !metadata.duration.isEmpty {\n                miniMetaItem(icon: \"clock\", text: metadata.duration)\n            }\n            if !metadata.cost.isEmpty {\n                miniMetaItem(icon: \"dollarsign.circle\", text: metadata.cost)\n            }\n            Spacer()\n        }\n    }\n    \n    private func miniMetaItem(icon: String, text: String) -> some View {\n        HStack(spacing: 3) {\n            Image(systemName: icon)\n                .font(.system(size: 8, weight: .medium))\n            Text(text)\n                .font(.system(size: 10))\n        }\n        .foregroundStyle(.white.opacity(0.45))\n        .padding(.horizontal, 6)\n        .padding(.vertical, 2)\n        .background(Color.white.opacity(0.06), in: Capsule())\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### File: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift` (SiriResponseWindowManager)\n\n4. **Thread metadata through `showChat()`** and `createOrUpdate()`:\n\n```swift\nfunc showChat(session: ChatSession, bubbleManager: SmartInputWindowManager, metadata: SessionMetadata? = nil) {\n    // ... existing message extraction ...\n    showMessages(Array(messages), bubbleManager: bubbleManager, metadata: metadata)\n}\n\nfunc showMessages(_ messages: [MiniChatMessage], bubbleManager: SmartInputWindowManager, isLoading: Bool = false, metadata: SessionMetadata? = nil) {\n    self.currentMetadata = metadata\n    // ... rest unchanged ...\n}\n```\n\n5. **Store metadata on `SiriResponseWindowManager`**:\n\n```swift\nprivate(set) var currentMetadata: SessionMetadata? = nil\n```\n\n#### File: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift` (pollMessages)\n\n6. **Pass metadata from ChatPlugin** in `pollMessages()`:\n\n```swift\n// In pollMessages(), when calling showChat:\nSiriResponseWindowManager.shared.showChat(\n    session: session,\n    bubbleManager: self,\n    metadata: chatPlugin?.sessionMetadata  // Pass the metadata from ChatPlugin\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Feature 4: Toggle Button in Toolbar\n\n**Goal**: A button in the bottom toolbar (quick actions row) to quickly toggle the mini panel open/closed.\n\n#### File: `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Components/InputBarContent.swift`\n\n1. **Add a `miniPanelToggleButton`** in the `quickActionsRow`. Place it at the right side, before the mic button (the mini panel is a \"chat peek\" feature, logically near the send area):\n\n```swift\n// In quickActionsRow (around line 361-384):\nprivate var quickActionsRow: some View {\n    HStack(spacing: 8) {\n        // ... existing model/mode/think pickers, context, suggestions, browser, screenshot ...\n        \n        Spacer()\n        \n        miniPanelToggleButton   // NEW -- before mic and send\n        micButton\n        sendOrStopButton\n    }\n    .padding(.horizontal, 20)\n    .padding(.top, 6)\n    .padding(.bottom, isFloating ? 10 : 6)\n}\n```\n\n2. **Define the `miniPanelToggleButton` view**:\n\n```swift\nprivate var miniPanelToggleButton: some View {\n    let isVisible = SiriResponseWindowManager.shared.panel?.isVisible ?? false\n    return Button {\n        if isVisible {\n            SiriResponseWindowManager.shared.dismiss()\n        } else {\n            // Re-show the mini panel with current chat state\n            if let plugin = chatPlugin,\n               let session = plugin.selectedSession {\n                let messages = session.messages\n                    .filter { $0.role != .system }\n                    .map { MiniChatMessage(role: $0.role == .user ? .user : .assistant, content: $0.content) }\n                if !messages.isEmpty {\n                    SiriResponseWindowManager.shared.showMessages(\n                        messages,\n                        bubbleManager: SmartInputWindowManager.shared,\n                        metadata: plugin.sessionMetadata\n                    )\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    } label: {\n        Image(systemName: isVisible ? \"bubble.left.and.bubble.right.fill\" : \"bubble.left.and.bubble.right\")\n            .font(.system(size: 11, weight: .medium))\n            .foregroundStyle(isVisible ? .white : .white.opacity(0.35))\n            .frame(width: 28, height: 28)\n            .contentShape(Circle())\n            .background(.ultraThinMaterial, in: Circle())\n            .overlay(Circle().fill(Color.white.opacity(isVisible ? 0.07 : 0.0)).allowsHitTesting(false))\n            .overlay(Circle().strokeBorder(\n                LinearGradient(colors: [Color.white.opacity(0.12)],\n                               startPoint: .leading, endPoint: .trailing),\n                lineWidth: 0.75\n            ).allowsHitTesting(false))\n    }\n    .buttonStyle(.plain)\n    .glassTooltip(isVisible ? \"Hide chat preview\" : \"Show chat preview\")\n}\n```\n\n**Note**: Since `SiriResponseWindowManager.shared.panel?.isVisible` is not reactive (it is a computed property on the NSPanel), the button icon will not auto-update. Two approaches:\n\n**Approach A (Recommended)**: Add a `@Published var isMiniPanelVisible: Bool = false` to `SiriResponseWindowManager` and update it in `showMessages()` (`= true`), `dismiss()` (`= false`), and the panel's `completionHandler`. Then observe it in InputBarContent:\n\n```swift\n// In SiriResponseWindowManager:\n@Published var isMiniPanelVisible: Bool = false\n\n// In showMessages():\nisMiniPanelVisible = true\n\n// In dismiss():\nisMiniPanelVisible = false  // in the completion handler\n```\n\nThen in InputBarContent, observe it:\n```swift\n@ObservedObject private var miniPanelManager = SiriResponseWindowManager.shared\n// Use miniPanelManager.isMiniPanelVisible instead of checking panel?.isVisible\n```\n\n**Approach B**: Use a notification. But Approach A is cleaner since `SiriResponseWindowManager` is already a class.\n\nHowever, `SiriResponseWindowManager` is not currently `ObservableObject`. It needs to adopt the protocol:\n\n```swift\n@MainActor\nfinal class SiriResponseWindowManager: NSObject, ObservableObject {\n    // ... (add ObservableObject conformance)\n    @Published var isMiniPanelVisible: Bool = false\n    // ... rest unchanged\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Implementation Sequence\n\nThe work should be done in this order to minimize risk of regressions:\n\n1. **Make `SiriResponseWindowManager` conform to `ObservableObject`** and add `@Published isMiniPanelVisible`.\n2. **Feature 4 (Toggle button)** -- Simplest change, immediately testable. Add the button to the toolbar, wire up show/dismiss.\n3. **Feature 1 (Instant display)** -- Add `isLoading` parameter flow through `SiriResponseWindowManager` -> `MiniChatCard`. Add `MiniTypingIndicator`. Wire up `showPendingChat()` call in `InputBarContent.sendMessage()`.\n4. **Feature 3 (Status bar)** -- Add metadata parameter flow, add `MiniStatusBar` view. Simple, low risk.\n5. **Feature 2 (Typewriter)** -- Most complex. Add `TypewriterState`, wire into `MiniChatCard`, modify poll flow.\n\n### Key Constraints to Remember\n\n- **No `if/else` view swapping** in the floating panel -- use `ZStack + opacity` pattern to avoid NSHostingView crashes.\n- **No SwiftUI animations that change layout size** in the floating panel -- use `.transaction { $0.disablesAnimations = true }` where needed. The typewriter text growth is OK because it only changes text content within a ScrollView, not the panel frame.\n- **No NSAnimationContext for resize** -- the mini panel is a fixed 700x360 frame, so this is not an issue.\n- **`ClearHostingView` mask** updates on layout -- the mini panel uses `NSHostingView` directly (not `ClearHostingView`), so no mask concern.\n- **xcodeproj registration** -- No new files are created outside existing files, so no `.pbxproj` changes needed. All changes are modifications to existing files.\n\n---\n\n### Critical Files for Implementation\n\n- `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputWindowManager.swift` -- Contains SiriResponseWindowManager, MiniChatCard, MiniChatBubble, pollMessages, and the entire mini panel system. This is the primary file for Features 1, 2, 3, and the toggle wiring.\n- `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Components/InputBarContent.swift` -- Contains sendMessage() where instant display is triggered, and quickActionsRow where the toggle button goes. Primary file for Features 1 and 4.\n- `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Plugins/ChatPlugin/ChatPlugin.swift` -- Contains ChatPlugin.sendMessage() (the async call flow), SessionStatusBar (pattern to follow for MiniStatusBar), TypingIndicator (pattern to follow for MiniTypingIndicator), and sessionMetadata.\n- `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/OrchestraKit/Sources/OrchestraKit/Models/Models.swift` -- Contains SessionMetadata struct used by the status bar, and MiniChatMessage/ChatSession types.\n- `/Users/fadymondy/Sites/orchestra-agents/apps/swift/Shared/Sources/Shared/Services/SmartInputState.swift` -- SmartInputState singleton that may need a `miniPanelRequested` flag if we want the toggle state to persist across panel recreations."
